propLaneMgmtLECCurrentAddress.name: propLaneMgmtLECCurrentAddress
propLaneMgmtLECCurrentAddress.description: The actual address currently being used by the management LEC.

propLaneMgmtLECIfIndexMap.name: propLaneMgmtLECIfIndexMap
propLaneMgmtLECIfIndexMap.description: The corresponding entry in the interfaces table of MIB II

propLaneMgmtLECLecIndexMap.name: propLaneMgmtLECLecIndexMap
propLaneMgmtLECLecIndexMap.description: The corresponding entry in the ATM LEC MIB

propLaneElanConfTable.name: propLaneElanConfTable
propLaneElanConfTable.description: A table containing information about each ELAN.

propLaneElanConfEntry.name: propLaneElanConfEntry
propLaneElanConfEntry.description: An entry containing information about a particular ELAN.

propLaneElanConfIndex.name: propLaneElanConfIndex
propLaneElanConfIndex.description: Index into this table, matches the ELAN MIB elanConfIndex.

propLaneElanSecurity.name: propLaneElanSecurity
propLaneElanSecurity.description: The status of the ELAN security. open - a LEC can join this ELAN without any ELAN info closed - a LEC can ONLY join this ELAN if it has some ELAN info.

propLaneElanLesDiscovery.name: propLaneElanLesDiscovery
propLaneElanLesDiscovery.description: Determines how the ELAN discovers its LES. auto - LES discovered automatically if we have a Prop LES. manual - the user must enter a LES address.

propLaneElanLesRgstrType.name: propLaneElanLesRgstrType
propLaneElanLesRgstrType.description: The LES registration mode to be supported by LECS. autosense - the LECS will adopt the proprietary registration version from the first registering LES. single - the LECS will only allow a LES using the proprietary registration method. resilient - the LECS will only allow a LES using the proprietary registration method which supports resilient LESes. distributed - the LECS will only allow a LES using the proprietary registration method which supports LNNI phase 1 LESes.

propLaneElanLesActualRgstrType.name: propLaneElanLesActualRgstrType
propLaneElanLesActualRgstrType.description: The actual LES registration mode that the LECS has adopted. single - the LES has used the proprietary registration method with the LECS. resilient - the LES has used the proprietary registration method to register with the LECS. distrib - the LES has used the proprietary registration method to register with the LECS. none - the registration mode is undefined as no LES has registered yet.

propLaneElanMaximumActiveLes.name: propLaneElanMaximumActiveLes
propLaneElanMaximumActiveLes.description: The maximum number of active LES's for the ELAN. Can only be written when the propLaneElanLesType is distributed. If propLaneElanLesActualType is not distributed then reading will always return the value 1.

propLaneElanLesAddrForm.name: propLaneElanLesAddrForm
propLaneElanLesAddrForm.description: The method by which the LES address will be formulated. Can only be written when the propLaneElanLesType is distributed. groupAddr - a user-provided group address will be used roundRobin - the address will be picked on a round robin basis longMatch - the longest matching LES address will be used.

propLaneElanGroupLesAddress.name: propLaneElanGroupLesAddress
propLaneElanGroupLesAddress.description: The group LES address of the ELAN. Can only be written when the propLaneElanLesType is distributed.

propLaneElanLuni2capability.name: propLaneElanLuni2capability
propLaneElanLuni2capability.description: The configured LUNI 2 capability of the ELAN. If yes, then the ELAN is LUNI 2 capable, and LECs using either LANE 1 or LUNI 2 can join the ELAN. If no, then LUNI 2 clients will be told to use LANE 1 instead of LUNI 2. If auto, then the capability is determined by the capability of the first LES to register for the ELAN (auto-register ELANs only).

propLaneElanLuni2capabilityOper.name: propLaneElanLuni2capabilityOper
propLaneElanLuni2capabilityOper.description: The detected LUNI 2 capability of the ELAN. If yes, then the ELAN is LUNI 2 capable, and LECs using either LANE 1 or LUNI 2 can join the ELAN. If no, then LUNI 2 clients will be told to use LANE 1 instead of LUNI 2. Auto is an interim state which indicates that the ELAN capability will be determined by the first LES to register the ELAN, and it has not been autodetected yet.

propLaneElanLesTable.name: propLaneElanLesTable
propLaneElanLesTable.description: A table containing information about each LES of an ELAN.

propLaneElanLesTableEntry.name: propLaneElanLesTableEntry
propLaneElanLesTableEntry.description: An entry containing information about a particular LES of an ELAN.

propLaneElanLesIndex.name: propLaneElanLesIndex
propLaneElanLesIndex.description: Index into this table, matches the ELAN MIB elanLesIndex.

propLaneElanLesLecIdLow.name: propLaneElanLesLecIdLow
propLaneElanLesLecIdLow.description: The lower end of the LES LEC ID range.

propLaneElanLesLecIdHigh.name: propLaneElanLesLecIdHigh
propLaneElanLesLecIdHigh.description: The higher end of the LES LEC ID range.

propLaneLesConfTable.name: propLaneLesConfTable
propLaneLesConfTable.description: A table containing information about each LES.

propLaneLesConfEntry.name: propLaneLesConfEntry
propLaneLesConfEntry.description: An entry containing information about a particular LES.

propLaneLesConfIndex.name: propLaneLesConfIndex
propLaneLesConfIndex.description: Index into this table, matches the LES MIB lesConfIndex.

propLaneLesMode.name: propLaneLesMode
propLaneLesMode.description: The LES registration mode. manual - the LES is ATM Forum compliant as per LANE v1.0 and will not attempt to register with the LECS. This means that management must tell the LECS the address of the LES. single - the LES will use a proprietary registration method. resilient - the LES will use a proprietary registration method. distrib - the LES will use a proprietary registration method, and can register with a LNNI phase 1 or better Prop LECS.

propLaneLesActiveStatus.name: propLaneLesActiveStatus
propLaneLesActiveStatus.description: The LES active status. active - the LES has resilient capability and is ACTIVE. standby - the LES has resilient capability and is on STANDBY. not-registered - the LES has resilient capability but is not yet registered. none - the LES doesn't have resilient capability.

propLaneLesLecIdLow.name: propLaneLesLecIdLow
propLaneLesLecIdLow.description: The lower end of the LES LEC ID range.

propLaneLesLecIdHigh.name: propLaneLesLecIdHigh
propLaneLesLecIdHigh.description: The higher end of the LES LEC ID range.

propLaneLesBusUnicastFilter.name: propLaneLesBusUnicastFilter
propLaneLesBusUnicastFilter.description: Whether BUS filter unicast filtering is enabled or disabled.

propLaneLesLuni2capability.name: propLaneLesLuni2capability
propLaneLesLuni2capability.description: The configured LUNI 2 capability of the LES. If yes, then the LES is LUNI 2 capable, and LECs using either LANE 1 or LUNI 2 can join the ELAN. If no, then LUNI 2 clients will be told to use LANE 1 instead of LUNI 2. Default value is yes (2).

propLaneLesLecTable.name: propLaneLesLecTable
propLaneLesLecTable.description: A table containing information about each LEC of a LES.

propLaneLesLecEntry.name: propLaneLesLecEntry
propLaneLesLecEntry.description: An entry containing information about a particular LEC of a LES.

propLaneLesLecIndex.name: propLaneLesLecIndex
propLaneLesLecIndex.description: Index into this table, matches the LES MIB lesLecIndex.

propLaneLesLecLuni2granted.name: propLaneLesLecLuni2granted
propLaneLesLecLuni2granted.description: Whether the LEC joined the LES as a LUNI2 client or a LANE v1 client.

propLaneLesLecSelectiveMulticast.name: propLaneLesLecSelectiveMulticast
propLaneLesLecSelectiveMulticast.description: Whether the LEC joined the LES requesting selective multicast.

propLaneLecsTable.name: propLaneLecsTable
propLaneLecsTable.description: A table containing information about a LECS in a Slot.

propLaneLecsEntry.name: propLaneLecsEntry
propLaneLecsEntry.description: An entry containing information about a LECS.

propLaneLecsLocation.name: propLaneLecsLocation
propLaneLecsLocation.description: The LECS location. local-wka - The LECS is local at the WKA. local-selector - The LECS is local. remote-wka - The LECS is remote at the WKA. remote-atm-addr - The LECS is remote at the address given in RemoteAddress below. remote-res-lecs - The LECS is a remote resilient LECS, found at the address given below. By setting location to remote, this implies that this device IS NOT taking part in the resilient LECS scheme itself.

propLaneLecsDefTRElan.name: propLaneLecsDefTRElan
propLaneLecsDefTRElan.description: The name of the default TR ELAN.

propLaneLecsDefEthElan.name: propLaneLecsDefEthElan
propLaneLecsDefEthElan.description: The name of the default ethernet ELAN.

propLaneLecsDefUnspecElan.name: propLaneLecsDefUnspecElan
propLaneLecsDefUnspecElan.description: The name of the default unspecified ELAN.

propLaneLecsResilientNetStatus.name: propLaneLecsResilientNetStatus
propLaneLecsResilientNetStatus.description: Status of the resilient LECS network as a whole. discovering - The algorithm is trying to find all participating devices in the scheme. forming - The algorithm is trying to contact each device. synchronising - The algorithm is checking that all parties have connectivity to all other parties. running - The scheme is running normally. not-resilient - This device is not taking part in the resilient scheme.

propLaneLecsResilientMode.name: propLaneLecsResilientMode
propLaneLecsResilientMode.description: Whether this LECS is taking part in the resilient LECS election scheme.

propLaneLecsResilientStatus.name: propLaneLecsResilientStatus
propLaneLecsResilientStatus.description: Status of this LECS in the resilient scheme.

propLaneLecsResilientPriority.name: propLaneLecsResilientPriority
propLaneLecsResilientPriority.description: LECS priority in the resilient scheme.

propLaneLecsResTable.name: propLaneLecsResTable
propLaneLecsResTable.description: A table containing information about each LECS in the resilient LECS scheme.

propLaneLecsResEntry.name: propLaneLecsResEntry
propLaneLecsResEntry.description: An entry containing information about a particular LECS in the resilient scheme.

propLaneLecsResAddress.name: propLaneLecsResAddress
propLaneLecsResAddress.description: The ATM address of this resilient LECS.

propLaneLecsResPriority.name: propLaneLecsResPriority
propLaneLecsResPriority.description: The priority of this LECS in the scheme.

propLaneLecsResStatus.name: propLaneLecsResStatus
propLaneLecsResStatus.description: The resilient status and link status of this LECS from the viewpoint of this agent. - timing-out means this agent has temporarily failed to contact the LECS. - not-found means that either communication to the LECS has timed-out, or that the LECS has never been found.

propLaneLecsResRowStatus.name: propLaneLecsResRowStatus
propLaneLecsResRowStatus.description: The status of this entry. For row creation (currently unsupported) : The manager should first set this field to undercreation(2) before setting any of the other fields. When all values required have been given it shoud be set to valid(3). If insufficient entries have been given when it is set to valid(3) then the agent will reject the request with BAD_VALUE.

propLaneLecsResActiveTime.name: propLaneLecsResActiveTime
propLaneLecsResActiveTime.description: The time in centiseconds since this RLECS last transitioned to active. Only non-zero values are valid here; a zero value meaning that either the RLECS was never active, or that no info is available for it.

propLaneLecsResAddrForm.name: propLaneLecsResAddrForm
propLaneLecsResAddrForm.description: The type of address that this LECS will use when it is active. Selector means switch address plus the selector given below.

propLaneLecsResSelector.name: propLaneLecsResSelector
propLaneLecsResSelector.description: The selector if the LECS is using its switch address.

propLaneSlotTable.name: propLaneSlotTable
propLaneSlotTable.description: A table containing information about a LANE Server in a Slot of the ATM switch.

propLaneSlotEntry.name: propLaneSlotEntry
propLaneSlotEntry.description: An entry containing information about a particular Slot in the switch.

propLaneSlotElanConfNextId.name: propLaneSlotElanConfNextId
propLaneSlotElanConfNextId.description: The next available ELAN index in this Slot provided by the agent. The value of this object can be used as the index to the standard elanConfTable during creation. Instead of the standard elanConfNextId.

propLaneSlotLecsConfNextId.name: propLaneSlotLecsConfNextId
propLaneSlotLecsConfNextId.description: The next available LECS index in this Slot. The value of this object can be used as the index to the lecsTable during creation. Instead of the standard lecsConfNextId.

propLaneSlotLesConfNextId.name: propLaneSlotLesConfNextId
propLaneSlotLesConfNextId.description: The next available LES index in this Slot. The value of this object can be used as the index by the network manager to create an entry in the lesConfTable. Instead of the standard lesConfNextId.

propLaneSlotBusConfNextId.name: propLaneSlotBusConfNextId
propLaneSlotBusConfNextId.description: The next available BUS index in this Slot. The value of this object can be used as the index by the network manager to create an entry in the busConfTable. Instead of the standard busConfNextId.

propLaneSlotNextLesSelector.name: propLaneSlotNextLesSelector
propLaneSlotNextLesSelector.description: A suitable value for the next LES selector in this Slot.

propLaneSlotNextBusSelector.name: propLaneSlotNextBusSelector
propLaneSlotNextBusSelector.description: A suitable value for the next BUS selector in this Slot.

propLaneSlotNextLecsSelector.name: propLaneSlotNextLecsSelector
propLaneSlotNextLecsSelector.description: A suitable value for the next LECS selector in this Slot.
